					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">The bricks on the floor HAVE to be thick, otherwise it gets hard to tell that they are surrounded by water. In your first edit it actually kinda looks like the water is above the floor, making it look like some kind of wall instead. The original shadows and highlights do a great job at representing the relative depth of the whole scene, I honestly wouldn't remove any of it. A few palette tweaks might indeed help with the contrast though.</div>

